OL,5, Amazon has been fined 32m euros (#27m) 
OL,6, in France for "excessive" surveillance 
OL,7, of its workers, including measures the 
OL,8, data watchdog found to be illegal.     
OL,10,FThe CNIL said Amazon France Logistique,
OL,11,Fwhich manages warehouses, recorded data
OL,12,Fcaptured by workers' handheld scanners.
OL,14,FIt found Amazon tracked activity so    
OL,15,Fprecisely that it led to workers having
OL,16,Fto potentially justify each break.     
OL,18,FAmazon said it strongly disagreed with 
OL,19,Fthe CNIL's findings and called them    
OL,20,F"factually incorrect".                 
